Description: Steatite shabti of the head of estate-workers Renusenebef with incised detail: a striated lappet-wig, a modelled face, a collar that covers the shoulders, a pectoral above a representation of Nut and parallel hands in relief holding two hoes; the leg section is inscribed with Chapter 6 of The Book of The Dead in one central column and seven rows of incised Hieroglyphs.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Louis, Duc de Blacas d'Aulps
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Louis, Duc de Blacas d'Aulps
